HEADWORD: Dare-devil
<hw>Dare"-dev`il</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A reckless
fellow. Also used adjectively; <as>as, <ex>dare-devil</ex>
excitement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A humorous <qex>dare-devil</qex> -- the very man⟦br⟧
To suit my prpose.</q> <rj><qau>Ld. Lytton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dare-deviltry</ent>⟦br⟧
